sections.content:
In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires—
(1) "export of services" means the supply of any service when—
(a) the supplier of service is located in India;
(b) the recipient of service is located outside India;
(c) the place of supply of service is outside India;
(d) the payment for such service has been received in convertible foreign exchange; and
(e) the supplier and recipient are not merely establishments of a distinct person.
